---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'SafetyWing in Mexico', level: 2 },
  { id: 'no-visa-requirement', text: 'No Visa Requirement', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-types', text: 'Coverage Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'using-in-mexico', text: 'Using SafetyWing in Mexico', level: 2 },
  { id: 'imss-combo', text: 'IMSS + SafetyWing Strategy', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose SafetyWing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Mexico', href: '/countries/mexico/insurance' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing vs Cigna', href: '/compare/safetywing-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'benefit', header: 'Benefit' },
  { key: 'nomad', header: 'Nomad Insurance' },
  { key: 'remote', header: 'Remote Health' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { benefit: 'Type', nomad: 'Travel Medical', remote: 'Health Insurance' },
  { benefit: 'Maximum Coverage', nomad: '$250,000', remote: '$1M-$10M' },
  { benefit: 'Outpatient', nomad: 'Emergency only', remote: 'Full coverage' },
  { benefit: 'Routine Care', nomad: 'Not covered', remote: 'Covered' },
  { benefit: 'Mental Health', nomad: 'Not covered', remote: 'Included' },
  { benefit: 'Pre-existing', nomad: 'Not covered', remote: 'After waiting period' },
  { benefit: 'US Coverage', nomad: 'Limited (15 days/90)', remote: 'Optional add-on' },
  { benefit: 'Commitment', nomad: 'None (cancel anytime)', remote: 'Monthly' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'age', header: 'Age' },
  { key: 'nomad', header: 'Nomad Insurance' },
  { key: 'remote', header: 'Remote Health' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { age: '25-39', nomad: '$45/4 weeks (~$49/mo)', remote: '$100-200/mo' },
  { age: '40-49', nomad: '$76/4 weeks (~$83/mo)', remote: '$150-300/mo' },
  { age: '50-59', nomad: '$117/4 weeks (~$127/mo)', remote: '$250-450/mo' },
  { age: '60-69', nomad: '$189/4 weeks (~$205/mo)', remote: '$400-700/mo' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'approach', header: 'Approach' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly Cost (Age 35)' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'What You Get' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { approach: 'IMSS only', monthly: '~$40', coverage: 'Public healthcare in Spanish' },
  { approach: 'SafetyWing Nomad only', monthly: '~$49', coverage: 'Emergency/travel backup' },
  { approach: 'IMSS + SafetyWing', monthly: '~$89', coverage: 'Routine + emergency + travel' },
  { approach: 'Remote Health only', monthly: '~$150', coverage: 'Comprehensive international' },
  { approach: 'Cigna Gold (excl USA)', monthly: '~$180', coverage: 'Full international coverage' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing Insurance in Mexico"
  description="Guide to using SafetyWing in Mexico. Perfect for digital nomads and budget-conscious expats. No visa requirements, affordable pricing, and IMSS combo strategy."
  headline="SafetyWing Insurance in Mexico"
  subheadline="The digital nomad favorite works great in Mexico. No visa insurance requirements + affordable IMSS combo = perfect for budget-conscious expats."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/mexico-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a SafetyWing Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/safetywing"
>
  <h2 id="overview">SafetyWing in Mexico</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing is the go-to insurance for digital nomads, and Mexico is one of their most popular destinations. Unlike European countries with strict visa insurance requirements, Mexico lets you combine SafetyWing's affordable coverage with IMSS public insurance for a comprehensive, budget-friendly healthcare strategy.
  </p>
  <p>
    For under $100/month total, you can have IMSS for routine care and SafetyWing for emergencies, travel, and private hospital access—a setup that works remarkably well for the digital nomad lifestyle.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$45</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Per 4 weeks (Nomad, age 30)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">180+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Countries covered</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">0</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Commitment required</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="no-visa-requirement">No Visa Requirement</h2>

  <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">Good News: No Insurance Required</h3>
    <p class="text-green-800">
      Unlike Spain or Portugal, <strong>Mexico does not require health insurance for residency visas.</strong> This means SafetyWing Nomad Insurance works fine here—you're not trying to meet visa requirements that demand comprehensive coverage. Choose insurance based on your actual needs, not bureaucratic requirements.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3>Visa Requirements (Financial Only)</h3>
  <p>
    Mexico's temporary and permanent residency visas require financial proof only:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Income proof:</strong> ~$3,738 USD/month for past 6 months, OR</li>
    <li><strong>Savings proof:</strong> ~$73,258 USD in bank accounts for past 12 months</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    No health insurance documentation needed. Use whatever coverage makes sense for your situation.
  </p>

  <h2 id="coverage-types">Coverage Options</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing offers two products. Understanding the difference matters.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance (Travel Medical)</h3>
  <p>
    This is SafetyWing's famous product—subscription-based travel medical insurance. It covers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Emergency medical treatment</li>
    <li>Acute illness that arises while traveling</li>
    <li>Accidents and injuries</li>
    <li>Emergency dental (pain relief only, up to $1,000)</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation up to $100,000</li>
    <li>Lost baggage, travel delays</li>
    <li>Limited US coverage (15 days per 90-day period)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>What Nomad Insurance Doesn't Cover</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Routine doctor visits</li>
    <li>Ongoing prescriptions</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Mental health</li>
    <li>Maternity</li>
    <li>Dental (except emergency)</li>
    <li>Preventive care</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    In Mexico, you can fill these gaps with IMSS (routine care) or pay out of pocket (Mexican healthcare is affordable).
  </p>

  <h3>Remote Health (Full Health Insurance)</h3>
  <p>
    Remote Health is comprehensive health insurance—a completely different product:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Coverage up to $10 million</li>
    <li>Full outpatient care</li>
    <li>Mental health included</li>
    <li>Maternity available (12-month wait)</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions (24-month wait)</li>
    <li>Optional US coverage add-on</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Simple Subscription Coverage"
    description="No commitment, cancel anytime. Perfect for the nomad lifestyle."
    buttonText="Learn More"
    buttonHref="/providers/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing's pricing is simple and transparent.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance Pricing</h3>
  <p>
    Billed every 4 weeks with no commitment:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Age-based pricing only</li>
    <li>$250 deductible per incident</li>
    <li>One child under 10 free per adult</li>
    <li>Cancel anytime—no penalties</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Remote Health Pricing</h3>
  <p>
    Monthly billing with more variables:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Age affects pricing significantly</li>
    <li>Deductible options: $0-$5,000</li>
    <li>US coverage is optional add-on (significant premium increase)</li>
    <li>Higher premiums but comprehensive coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="using-in-mexico">Using SafetyWing in Mexico</h2>

  <h3>Finding Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing doesn't have a traditional provider network. Use any licensed provider in Mexico:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Private hospitals (ABC, Médica Sur, Hospital Ángeles)</li>
    <li>Private clinics</li>
    <li>English-speaking doctors (common in expat areas)</li>
    <li>Urgent care centers</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
    <li>Pay the Mexican provider upfront</li>
    <li>Get itemized receipt (factura)</li>
    <li>Submit claim via SafetyWing portal</li>
    <li>Wait 10-30 days for reimbursement</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    Direct billing is limited. Expect to pay and file for reimbursement for most care.
  </p>

  <h3>Mexican Healthcare Costs</h3>
  <p>
    Good news: Mexican healthcare is affordable. If you're paying out of pocket for routine care:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Doctor visit: $30-60</li>
    <li>Specialist: $50-100</li>
    <li>Lab work: $20-50</li>
    <li>Dental cleaning: $30-50</li>
    <li>Urgent care: $50-100</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    SafetyWing's $250 deductible is reasonable given these prices. Pay for routine care yourself, use SafetyWing for emergencies.
  </p>

  <h2 id="imss-combo">IMSS + SafetyWing Strategy</h2>
  <p>
    The smartest budget strategy for Mexico combines IMSS and SafetyWing:
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">The Budget Combo</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
      <li><strong>IMSS (~$40/mo under 60):</strong> Routine care, prescriptions, basic coverage</li>
      <li><strong>SafetyWing Nomad (~$49/mo):</strong> Emergencies, private hospitals, travel, evacuation</li>
      <li><strong>Total: ~$89/month</strong> for comprehensive coverage</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>When to Use Each</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>IMSS:</strong> Routine doctor visits, generic medications, basic lab work</li>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Emergency room, private hospitals, English-speaking doctors, travel outside Mexico</li>
    <li><strong>Out of pocket:</strong> Specialists, dental, quick private consultations</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Why This Works</h3>
  <p>
    IMSS gives you a healthcare home base in Mexico—a reliable place for routine care at virtually no cost. SafetyWing covers the gaps: emergencies, private hospital access, and travel coverage when you leave Mexico. Together, they cost less than most comprehensive international plans.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose SafetyWing</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Nomad Insurance Good For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Digital nomads in Mexico</li>
        <li>Young, healthy expats (under 40)</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious travelers</li>
        <li>Those who travel frequently</li>
        <li>People comfortable with IMSS for routine care</li>
        <li>Those testing Mexico before committing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Remote Health Good For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
        <li>Long-term expats wanting more coverage</li>
        <li>Those with mental health needs</li>
        <li>People wanting comprehensive protection</li>
        <li>Subscription model preference</li>
        <li>Those who don't want IMSS</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Consider Alternatives If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>You're American wanting US coverage:</strong> <a href="/countries/mexico/insurance/aetna-international">Aetna</a> or <a href="/countries/mexico/insurance/geoblue">GeoBlue</a> include US networks</li>
    <li><strong>You have pre-existing conditions:</strong> Nomad Insurance doesn't cover them</li>
    <li><strong>You're over 50:</strong> Consider more comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>You need mental health care:</strong> Nomad doesn't cover it (Remote Health does)</li>
    <li><strong>You want direct billing:</strong> SafetyWing is mostly reimbursement-based</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Perfect for Digital Nomads"
    description="Affordable coverage with no commitment. Pair with IMSS for complete protection."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/safetywing"
  />

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Can I use SafetyWing as my only insurance in Mexico?</h3>
  <p>
    You can, but it's not ideal for long-term stays. Nomad Insurance only covers emergencies, not routine care. Combine with IMSS for routine care, or consider Remote Health for comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Does SafetyWing cover me visiting the US from Mexico?</h3>
  <p>
    Nomad Insurance includes limited US coverage—15 days per 90-day period. For longer US visits, you'd need additional coverage. If you regularly visit the US, consider Aetna or GeoBlue instead.
  </p>

  <h3>What's the SafetyWing claims experience like?</h3>
  <p>
    Mixed reviews. Simple online process, but some users report delays and claims requiring appeals. Document everything thoroughly. For straightforward emergency claims, most users report positive experiences.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I get IMSS as a temporary resident?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. IMSS is available to temporary residents (Residente Temporal) and permanent residents. Tourists on FMM visitor permits are not eligible. You need to be a legal resident.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I get SafetyWing or Remote Health?</h3>
  <p>
    For most digital nomads in Mexico: Nomad Insurance + IMSS is the best value combo. If you want comprehensive coverage without IMSS, need mental health coverage, or have ongoing health needs, Remote Health is worth the higher cost.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I need evacuation?</h3>
  <p>
    Both Nomad Insurance ($100,000) and Remote Health include medical evacuation. If you live in a smaller Mexican town, this can be important for getting to major hospitals in Mexico City, Guadalajara, or the US.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Nomad Coverage?"
    description="No commitment, no paperwork. Start in minutes."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. SafetyWing's Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance, not comprehensive health insurance. IMSS enrollment requires legal residency. Verify all information before making decisions.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
